item.title: Jael Strauss, America’s Next Top Model Alum, Dead at 34
item.dc:creator: Kay Rhodes
item.description:
Reading Time: 3 minutesJael Strauss, the America’s Next Top Model contestant who revealed just two months ago that she had breast cancer, died …

Jael Strauss, America’s Next Top Model Alum, Dead at 34 was originally published on The Hollywood Gossip.
item.content:encoded:
Reading Time: 3 minutes

Jael Strauss, the America’s Next Top Model contestant who revealed just two months ago that she had breast cancer, died Tuesday morning around 11 a.m.

She was under hospice care at the time.

And she was 34 years old.

Insiders close to Strauss tell TMZ that her condition took a turn for the worse on Monday night, following several days during which Strauss was unconscious.

Her family has been allowing visitors to see Jael, however, up until the final few hours of her life.

It was clear at that point that the Season 8 hopeful did not have much time remaining.

Strauss chose to stop chemotherapy around Halloween and went into hospice on Thanksgiving, writing on Facebook:

"First night in hospice. So many things I never knew about life. Or death. So many things."

It was only a month or so before this transition that Strauss wrote a lengthy and emotional message to fans about her Stage IV breast cancer.

Likely aware at the time that the diagnosis was fatal, she said: "It has aggressively spread throughout my body and is incurable."

"With treatment it may prolong my life longer than the ‘few months’ doctors said I could make it. I don’t want to die."

"I need another one of those miracles that I got back in 2013."

With this statement, Strauss was referring to a past battling the devastating affects of crystal meth addiction.

This was something difficult and personal, and which she addressed publicly in an appearance on Dr. Phil in 2012.

In August, just two months before the breast cancer diagnosis, Strauss celebrated five years of sobriety.

This is what she wrote on Instagram in tribute to herself, her situation and all those who helped her along the way:

I know a few things to be true:

Miracles are real, Recovery is possible for everyone no matter how far gone you think you are, We are never too broken to be put back together.

Service work feels better than the greatest high.

Sobriety makes you weirder not normal and I’d be dead if it weren’t for all the love and forgiveness I’ve been showered with by my friends and family.

The Most Shocking and Sad Reality Star Deaths: Gone, But Not Forgotten

VIEW GALLERY

A GoFundMe was opened for Strauss about a month ago that has thus far raised more than $18,000 to fund her treatment.

SAid Jael’s family and friends to TMZ in a statement:

"The one blessing was that we were able to show her how loved she was before she passed. She brought so much light to people."

As mentioned above, Strauss competed on the eighth season of America’s Next Top Model in 2007 and finished sixth in the competition.

May Jael Strauss rest in peace.

item.title: Jael Strauss, America’s Next Top Model Alum, Has Stage IV Breast Cancer
item.dc:creator: Kay Rhodes
item.description:
Reading Time: 3 minutesI don’t want to die. These are the heartbreaking words penned by Jael Strauss on her Facebook page in a message …

Jael Strauss, America’s Next Top Model Alum, Has Stage IV Breast Cancer was originally published on The Hollywood Gossip.
item.content:encoded:
Reading Time: 3 minutes

I don’t want to die.

These are the heartbreaking words penned by Jael Strauss on her Facebook page in a message to fans that relayed the most painful news imaginable:

She has been diagnosed with an aggressive form of breast cancer.

“I was gonna write some long thing but some of you guys deserve to know,” the 34-year old wrote last week, four days into Breast Cancer Awareness month.

She then added very simply:

“On October 2nd I was diagnosed with stage IV breast cancer. It has aggressively spread throughout my body and is incurable.”

Stage IV is the final and most serious stage for cancer.

It is not always a death sentence, but as Strauss writes here, there is rarely any treatment options for someone that has contracted such an illness.

Strauss later confirmed that the name of her illness was rapidly progressive metastatic inflammatory breast cancer.

She went on to explain that undergoing chemotherapy and treatment may help extend her doctors’ original prognosis.

"With treatment it may prolong my life longer than the “few months” doctors said I could make it," she added.

"I don’t want to die. I need another one of those miracles that I got back in 2013."

Strauss competed on the eighth season of America’s Next Top Model in 2007, finishing six among all contestants.

Just this past August, she celebrated five years of sobriety, writing at the time on Instagram;

“Today I have 5 years sober. Good God!

"I know a few things to be true: Miracles are real, Recovery is possible for everyone no matter how far gone you think you are, We are never too broken to be put back together."

She talked years ago with Dr. Phil about how an intervention by her loved ones allowed her to overcome her addiction. 

(Hence the reference above to the year 2013.)

“Service work feels better than the greatest high, Sobriety makes you weirder not normal,” she continued last month.

“And I’d be dead if it weren’t for all the love and forgiveness I’ve been showered with by my friends and family. Thank you to anyone that’s ever let me sponsor them.”

To help offset some of the medical costs, Strauss’ friends have set up a GoFundMe page on her behalf, confirming that the former model has already started chemotherapy.

“What we do know is that Jael is putting all of her energy and drive into fighting this insidious disease and can use as much support and love as possible,” reads the fundraising page, noting that:

“Jael is in tremendous pain right now and is unable to work. In a month, she will be let go from her job and lose her health insurance.”

It adds:

Jael, being the selfless person that she is, has helped countless people throughout her life as an advocate for recovery and social justice.

She has offered everything she has to people in need; no matter what their situation, she is always ready to help with an empathetic heart and nonjudgmental spirit.

She has created “gofundmes” for literally dozens of her friends, and it is now time for us to pay her back.

We have the chance, and honestly the obligation, to step up and return the favor.

You can donate to her cause HERE.

The campaign has since raised over $7,800 in three days.

“Currently fighting stage 4 inflammatory breast cancer,” reads Jael’s Instagram bio. “Plz send miracles."

We are doing just that.

item.title: America’s Next Top Model: Canceled by The CW!
item.dc:creator: Kay Rhodes
item.description:
Reading Time: < 1 minuteAnd now, for some news that is nothing to smize about: America’s Next Top Model is coming to an end. …

America’s Next Top Model: Canceled by The CW! was originally published on The Hollywood Gossip.
item.content:encoded:
Reading Time: < 1 minute

And now, for some news that is nothing to smize about:

America’s Next Top Model is coming to an end.

With only a few of episodes remaining until Tyra Banks crowns the winner of America’s Next Top Model Cycle 22, the iconic model has came out on Wednesday and said she’s prepared to wrap up the long-running reality program.

For good.

"TYRA MAIL! Thinking #ANTM22 should be our last cycle. I truly believe it’s time. May your pics be forever fierce. Keep on Smizing!" Banks wrote.

It’s unclear whether Tyra truly arrived at this decision on her own or whether The CW basically canceled the fashion-based competition.

Either way, the series finale will now air on December 4 at 9/8c.

According to a CW source, the network is planning a retrospective special for some time in 2016.

"America’s Next Top Model was a successful franchise for two networks, first at UPN and then The CW, and it became not just a ratings hit, but a global pop culture phenomenon," said Mark Pedowitz, President of the CW, in a statement.

"I want to thank Tyra and Ken for all their years of success in establishing a show that was not just popular in the U.S., but all across the world."

item.title: Tyra Banks: Rebranding Herself as Futuristic Business Woman With Pixie Cut!
item.dc:creator: Fantasia Glitzhips
item.description:
Reading Time: 2 minutesTyra Banks is changing it up with a chic pixie cut.  Cutting your hair isn’t easy for a supermodel. One …

Tyra Banks: Rebranding Herself as Futuristic Business Woman With Pixie Cut! was originally published on The Hollywood Gossip.
item.content:encoded:
Reading Time: 2 minutes

Tyra Banks is changing it up with a chic pixie cut. 

Cutting your hair isn’t easy for a supermodel. One bad alteration could damage a career.

But Tyra said f*ck it, and chopped it all off.

In an interview with People Magazine, Tyra explains what made her drastically change her look.

Banks says, “I come from the school of hardcore branding and if you are known for something keep that because that is what the public connects you with.”

She continues, “I had long, golden hair as a high-fashion model, and a Victoria’s Secret model and a Sports Illustrated model, and that’s how people know me. But great brands tweak their logos and change up their formula, and I said it’s time for me to do that.”

Posting photos of inspirational cuts on Instagram, it appears this may have been a tough choice for Banks.

But her mother’s positive reaction suggests that she may have supported her daughter’s decision.

“My mom keeps talking about my neck. She [mom] says, “They know you’ve got a neck now,” Banks shares.

We think Tyra looks fabulous with short hair. But Tyra is still getting used to it.

The supermodel and host of America’s Next Top Model says she feels “very exposed.”

However, that exposure is encouraging a new and improved version of Tyra.

According to Banks, the cut has forced her to “push those shoulders back” and change her style to outfits with “structure and angles.”

“Futuristic businesswoman is what I’m going for with this hair,” Banks explains. 

Using her hair for publicity is not a new strategy for Banks.  The last time her hair made the news, it was feeble attempt to connect with us regular folk.

After watching Tyra force tearful, young models to chop off their hair on episodes of ANTM, it is nice to see Tyra heed her own advice.

item.title: Mirjana Puhar: Mourned by Tyra Banks, America’s Next Top Model Producer
item.dc:creator: Kay Rhodes
item.description:
Reading Time: < 1 minuteA day after news broke that Mirjana Puhar was tragically killed in a triple homicide, Tyra Banks has paid tribute to …

Mirjana Puhar: Mourned by Tyra Banks, America’s Next Top Model Producer was originally published on The Hollywood Gossip.
item.content:encoded:
Reading Time: < 1 minute

A day after news broke that Mirjana Puhar was tragically killed in a triple homicide, Tyra Banks has paid tribute to the former America’s Next Top Model contestant.

“We are deeply saddened to learn of the tragic news about Mirjana Puhar. She was a vivacious and promising young woman,” Banks and fellow executive producer Ken Mok said, adding:

"Our hearts and prayers go out to her loved ones.”

Tyra also sent out a tweet about the tragedy. It reads:

The Top Model family is deeply saddened by the tragic news of Mirjana Puhar. We love you, Mirjana. Forever.

Puhar, only 19 years old, was found dead alongside her boyfriend and one other victim inside her boyfriend’s home in Charlotte on Tuesday.

Authorities have not yet released any information about potential suspects or the identity of the third victim in this very said incident.

We’ll update this story when more news breaks and we also send our thoughts and prayers to the loved ones of Mirjana Puhar.

item.title: Mirjana Puhar: America’s Next Top Model Contestant Murdered in Triple Homicide
item.dc:creator: Tyler Johnson
item.description:
Reading Time: < 1 minuteMirjana Puhar – a contestant on the most recent season of America’s Next Top Model – was murdered yesterday in an apparent triple …

Mirjana Puhar: America’s Next Top Model Contestant Murdered in Triple Homicide was originally published on The Hollywood Gossip.
item.content:encoded:
Reading Time: < 1 minute

Mirjana Puhar – a contestant on the most recent season of America’s Next Top Model – was murdered yesterday in an apparent triple homicide in Charlotte, North Carolina.

TMZ is reporting that the 19-year-old Puhar was found dead alongside her boyfriend and one other victim inside the boyfriend’s home.

Sources say a friend discovered the bodies of Puhar and her boyfriend when she entered the house after hearing gunshots.

The third body was found when police responded to a 911 call.

A native of Serbia, Mirjana Puhar fled to the United States with her family during the Kosovo War when she was just five years old.

After dropping out of high school, Puhar reportedly worked a variety of low-paying jobs before entering the world of modeling.

She was featured in the 21st cycle of ANTM at the age of 18.

She made headlines at the time as the youngest member of the cast, and she formed a romantic relationship with a male model during her time on the show.

However, it is believed that the boyfriend who was murdered Tuesday is not the man that Puhar dated on the long-running reality program.

Police have not released any information regarding suspects or the identity of the third victim in this tragedy at this time in what is a developing story.

We will have more details as they become available …

item.title: Renee Alway, America’s Next Top Model Star, Busted For Burglary, Forgery, Drugs, …
item.dc:creator: Free Britney
item.description:
Reading Time: < 1 minuteOne-time America’s Next Top Model star Renee Alway was arrested following a SIX-HOUR STANDOFF with police, according to reports. Why? …

Renee Alway, America’s Next Top Model Star, Busted For Burglary, Forgery, Drugs, … was originally published on The Hollywood Gossip.
item.content:encoded:
Reading Time: < 1 minute

One-time America’s Next Top Model star Renee Alway was arrested following a SIX-HOUR STANDOFF with police, according to reports. Why?

Alway, who finished third on ANTM Cycle 8, was arrested on June 28 in Palm Springs, Calif., and slapped with a ton of charges … to say the least.

She was busted for suspicion of burglary, fraud, possession of narcotics, forged bills, and committing a felony while on bail (!) to name just a few.

Police were called about a suspicious female lurking around a house that was supposed to be vacant; there, they found Alway in the garage with a gun.

 

Officers had reason to believe another person, a male, was also in the house, and also packing heat, so they reportedly called in the SWAT team.

No one else was found inside after their sweep, but the 27-year-old Alway was booked and remains behind bars now, unable to post $150,000 bail.

As for why she was out on bail the first time, Renee Alway was arrested back on June 2 for possession of drug paraphernalia, petty theft, and fraud.

She pleaded not guilty, and was released on bail … then this above incident took place four weeks later, landing her back in the pokey again. Insane.

item.content:encoded:
Reading Time: < 1 minute

And… we have a winner!

With Kiara Belen, Laura James and the returning Leila Goldkuhl the trio of contestants remaining last night on the America’s Next Top Model finale, the ladies were tasked with photo shoots for sponsors Nine West and Nylon.

They then strutted down a haunted house-themed runway.

Who was able – in Tyra’s actual words – to “reclaim her immortal smize?”

LAURA JAMES!

“I’ve been dreaming of this for such a long time,” James said upon earning the title and winning $130,000; a spread in Nylon; and a contract with two model agencies.

As the champion of the first-ever college cycle, Laura also be the face of the fragrance, Dream Come True.

Is she a deserving winner?

item.title: America’s Next Top Model to Return for 20th Cycle, Feature MEN!
item.dc:creator: Kay Rhodes
item.description:

America’s Next Top Model to Return for 20th Cycle, Feature MEN! was originally published on The Hollywood Gossip.
item.content:encoded:
Reading Time: < 1 minute

America’s Next Top Model will reach a milestone next summer.

The reality series has been renewed for a 20th cycle and will return to The CW in mid-2013, but with a pretty major twist:

Men will actually compete against women this time around! Prepare those looks of Blue Steel, fellas.

America’s Next Top Model has been banished to Friday nights by the network and is in the middle of its 19th season. This edition features college students vying for a cash prize and a modeling contract.

It also features Tyra Banks, as self-serving an as irritating as ever.
